# Beautiful To-Do List with Theme Toggle

This project is a responsive and interactive to-do list web application with a theme toggle feature. Users can add tasks, drag and drop them between different status columns, and switch between dark and light themes.

## Features

- Add new tasks to the "To Do" list
- Drag and drop tasks between "To Do", "In Progress", and "Done" columns
- Toggle between dark and light themes
- Responsive design for various screen sizes
- Smooth transitions when changing themes

## Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (ES6+)

## How to Use

1. Clone this repository or download the HTML file.
2. Open the HTML file in a web browser.
3. To add a new task:
   - Type the task in the input field under the "To Do" column
   - Click the "Add Task" button or press Enter
4. To move a task:
   - Click and drag the task to another column
5. To switch themes:
   - Click the toggle switch in the upper right corner

## Customization

You can easily customize the colors and styles by modifying the CSS variables in the `<style>` section of the HTML file. Look for the `.dark-theme` and `.light-theme` classes to adjust colors for each theme.

## Browser Compatibility

This application should work in all modern browsers that support HTML5 drag and drop API and CSS3 features.

